<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,571,886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,572,598]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Taxonomy</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[340,438,571,597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">holotype</typeStatus>
(NMW) has been examined by RAB. The species was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Browne 1974)" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Xyleborus partitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schedl, K. E." box="[240,400,607,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="117 - 124" refId="ref6549" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1980) Zur Synonymie der Borkenkafer. XXVIII. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 31 (1979), 117 - 124." type="journal article" year="1980">Schedl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, but restored as a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaver, R. A." box="[809,973,608,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref5359" refString="Beaver, R. A. (1991) New synonymy and taxonomic changes in Pacific Scolytidae (Coleoptera). Annalen des Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien, 92 B, 87 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Beaver (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[983,1276,607,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" refId="ref6101" refString="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2013) Xyleborini of New Guinea, a taxonomic monograph (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology, Entomological Society of America, Annapolis, Maryland, 172 pp." type="book" year="2013">Hulcr and Cognato (2013)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed the species, recognised that it could not be included in 
<emphasis box="[723,936,643,669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichhoff" authorityYear="1864" box="[723,837,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" species="sens">Xyleborus</taxonomicName>
sens. str
</emphasis>
., and included it under ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Conte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1204,1333,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xyleborini">Xyleborini</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">incertae sedis</emphasis>
’. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cognato, A. I. &amp; Smith, S. M. &amp; Beaver, R. A." box="[232,475,679,706]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="540 - 554" refId="ref5835" refString="Cognato, A. I., Smith, S. M. &amp; Beaver, R. A. (2020) Two new genera of Oriental xyleborine ambrosia beetles (Coleoptera, Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa, 4722 (6), 540 - 554. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4722.6.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Cognato 
<emphasis box="[335,392,679,705]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
in their phylogeny of 181 xyleborine species, showed that it lay on a branch distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichhoff" authorityYear="1864" box="[213,327,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[213,327,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Xyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beaver &amp; Petrov" authorityYear="2021" box="[909,1049,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Melanesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[909,1049,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Melanesicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apart from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beaver &amp; Petrov &amp; Sittichaya" authorityYear="2021" box="[1182,1352,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Melanesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nukuruanus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1352,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">M. nukuruanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the lack of distinct striae, and the irregular arrangement of granules on the elytral declivity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
